{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Pre-Commit Test Gate",
  "description": "Runs dotnet test before git commit to ensure all tests pass. Blocks commit if any test fails.",
  "version": "2",
  "when": {
    "type": "command",
    "command": "git commit"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Before committing, identify which project was modified and run its tests:\n\n1. Check `git diff --cached --name-only` to determine which project folder(s) changed.\n2. Use the build commands from .kiro/steering/multi-project.md:\n   - verification: `dotnet test src/Verification.sln`\n   - identification: `dotnet test src/Identification.sln`\n   - kyc-customer-due-diligence: `dotnet test src/CustomerDueDiligence.sln`\n   - cdd-business: `dotnet test src/KYC.CDD.sln`\n   - kyc-e-kyc-api: `dotnet test tests/`\n   - kyc-partner-api: `dotnet test DipChip.Test/`\n   - kyc-admin-portal: `dotnet test eKycApp/eKycApp.Test/`\n3. Run tests from the relevant project directory.\n4. If ALL tests pass, proceed with the commit.\n5. If any test FAILS:\n   - Show which test(s) failed and the error message\n   - Attempt to fix the failing test(s)\n   - Re-run tests to confirm the fix\n   - Only proceed with commit once all tests pass\n\nDo NOT skip this step. All tests must pass before committing."
  },
  "shortName": "pre-commit-test"
}
